P9-T1 root cause: src/main.ts:714 begins the chaingun hit-result loop, but the branch at src/main.ts:718-727 handles every chaingun hit as an asteroid. Enemy hits that reach zero health call handleAsteroidDestroyed instead of the enemy destruction path, so dead enemies are not removed from sectorObjects.enemies and enemy rewards/audio/death handling are skipped.
P10-T1 root cause: src/main.ts:976-979 built radarBlips with sectorObjects.asteroids before sectorObjects.enemies, while src/cockpit.ts:34 caps the cockpit blip pool at MAX_BLIPS = 20. Sectors spawn 25 asteroids (src/sector.ts:6) plus enemies, so asteroid contacts could consume every blip slot before enemy contacts rendered; the radar was not reading/displaying the authoritative enemy list directly.
